1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 28-32 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to the enforcement of agency rules; and to provide a report.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 28-32 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
5 and enacted as follows:
6 Agency enforcement of rules - Disclosure of authority - Report.
7 1. When enforcing a rule adopted under this chapter, including through an official notice,
8 determination, order, or similar action, an agency shall specifically reference the
9 statute or rule providing the authority upon which the agency's action is based.
10 2. If an agency is found to have exceeded its statutory authority, or if an agency's
11 determination is not affirmed by the court under section 28 - 32 - 46, the agency shal l
12 report the matter to the office of the governor, in a manner prescribed by the governor.
13 3. Any person may report a violation of this section to the office of the governor.
14 4. The office of the governor shall:
15 a. Investigate a reported violation of this section and take any necessary
16 disciplinary action, including issuing a written warning, implementing an
17 improvement plan, or terminating employment, as determined appropriate by the
18 office of the governor;
19 b. M aintain a record of a report received under this section, including
20 documentation regarding any investigative or disciplinary action taken by the
21 office of the governor or the agency in response to the report; and
22 c. Provide an annual report to the administrative rules committee which identifies
23 each agency involved in a violation reported under this section and the number of
24 reports against each identified agency.
